{"questionId":"21909","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>At Springfield University, the weights, in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>kg</mtext></math>, of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math> chinchilla rabbits and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math> sable rabbits&nbsp;were recorded. The aim was to find out whether chinchilla rabbits are generally heavier&nbsp;than sable rabbits. The results obtained are summarized in the following table.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/b1e213f96dbf222855d75358c52a1f0c30782be9.png\"></p>\n<p>A <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math>-test is to be performed at the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>%</mo></math> significance level.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>-value for this test.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>-value&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0408</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0408065</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A2</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for an answer of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>041565</mn><mo>…</mo></math>, from “unpooled” settings on GDC.</p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21909","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ2.8b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the p-value for this test.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Expected, observed, hypotheses, chi squared, gof, t-test"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}